Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @Potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%g}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the garlic, @Dried Rosemary{1}(crumbled), @Panko Breadcrumbs{10%g}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and @Water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs, then add the @British Pork Mince{240%g}. Season with pepper and mix together with your hands. Roll into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers onto another baking tray and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, add the @Cider Vinegar{15%ml} and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing to a medium bowl. Season with salt, pepper and a pinch of sugar (if you have any), then mix together and set the dressing aside. Quarter, core and thinly slice the @Apple{1}(thinly sliced) (no need to peel).

When the burgers are cooked, carefully place the cheese on top of the burgers and pop back into the oven until the cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @Burger Buns{2}. Pop them onto a baking tray and into oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, spread the @BBQ Sauce{64%g} over the bun bases and lids. Top the bases with the cheesy burgers and some @Wild Rocket{10%g}, then sandwich shut.

Add the remaining @Wild Rocket{10%g} and apple slices to the bowl of dressing and toss to coat.

> TIP: Keep a portion of salad aside before dressing for anyone who'd prefer it without.

Serve your burgers with the wedges and salad alongside.

Enjoy!